# ModelSpinSystem

## Purpose
Spins each 3D model entity about the world Y axis over time. Each frame it advances every
ModelSpinComponent's accumulated time by the frame delta and emits a ModelSpinTransformRequest
carrying the resulting rotation quaternion (and the entity's fixed anchor position), which the
SandboxApp TransformResolveSystem aggregates into the canonical resolved transform request. A model
with zero spin speed holds its initial orientation.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ModelSpinComponent | write | Per-model spin speed + accumulated time; the elapsed time is advanced in place |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| ModelSpinTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Position + Y-axis rotation request; aggregated by the SandboxApp TransformResolveSystem |
